01:38:31,150 --> 01:38:32,970
立正
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}Attention on deck!{\r}

1225
01:38:40,070 --> 01:38:41,980
有人曾問我...
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}Once somebody asked me...{\r}

1226
01:38:42,070 --> 01:38:44,480
公民和平民...
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}if I knew the difference between a citizen...{\r}

1227
01:38:44,580 --> 01:38:46,490
有何不同
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}and a civilian.{\r}

1228
01:38:46,580 --> 01:38:48,160
我現在知道了
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}I can tell you now.{\r}

1229
01:38:48,250 --> 01:38:50,320
公民有...
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}A citizen has the courage...{\r}

1230
01:38:50,420 --> 01:38:54,910
捍衛人類安全的勇氣
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}to make the safety of the human race their personal responsibility.{\r}

1231
01:38:59,090 --> 01:39:01,500
蒂絲是我朋友
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}Dizzy was my friend.{\r}

1232
01:39:01,590 --> 01:39:03,720
她也是戰士
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}She was a soldier.{\r}

1233
01:39:03,800 --> 01:39:05,680
更重要的是
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}But more than that...{\r}

1234
01:39:05,760 --> 01:39:08,170
她是聯邦公民
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}she was a citizen of the Federation.{\r}

1235
01:39:10,600 --> 01:39:12,510
敬禮
{\fntahoma\fs16\bord0\1c&H00FFFF&\b0}Present arms!{\r}

